Consent Management Question

> Vijaya, one of our fintech partners is complaining that our consent flow is too restrictive.

Customers must:

1. Authenticate with the bank


2. Review the data being shared


3. Select data categories


4. Approve the duration of access


5. Confirm consent



The fintech argues that every additional step reduces conversion and customer acquisition.

They want a single-click consent experience.

As Product Director, how would you decide whether to simplify the consent flow?




